  "doc_id": "3285",
  "text": "PGC-1α is another up-regulated gene involved in regulating of glucose metabolic process in the current study. It was a later-induced gene, whose expression was increased 4.3-fold at d 90. PGC-1α is a transcriptional coactivator with an important role in regulation of energy homeostasis [CITATION_1] . In skeletal muscle, PGC-1α promotes glucose uptake and expression of genes involved in the electron transport chain and oxidative phosphorylation [CITATION_2] . Therefore our finding provide new evidence that diet n-3 PUFA may improve insulin sensitivity in skeletal muscle.",
